reviews.text: Great Place.  Many wonderful memories from Boy Scouts, Indiana University days, shared family memories. Special moments of canoeing, skiing, sailing, swimming, walking across the ice, dating while at I.U., family time at the Inn, stargazing, conferences, even horseback riding.  This is where the name of the radio station “Shine 99” was thought up during a brain-storming session back in the fall of 1981.    :>)
Great lake..lots of bluegill and crappies
Had a great day boating and spending time with family on lake and at Paynetown Campgrounds. Grounds were clean. Womens showers were scalding hot tho. No cooling down in 90 degree heat. Still fun.
The kids had a great time camping at one of the primitive sites.

Lots of space to wander and good places to fish. No complaints about the lake or its environs, but some of the other visitors to the area on the weekend of 21JUL18 did their best to ruin it for everyone with trash and noise.

This is a local theater which maintains the small production feel while offering significant seating and impressive talent.  The interior is beautiful and classy, and the seating is comfortable with good views of the stage. Street parking is available in the area, or parking garages are located within a few blocks.
Very cool venue for unique shows and an excellent reputation in the world of entertainment.
Best venue for new plays bar none!
Bpp is a wonderful experience.
Excellent play and actors.
Amazing staff
The most beautiful place of the IU Music School
Indiana University's Simon Music Center has several resources for music students to study and is conveniently located on Indiana University campus.

Fascinating collection, beautifully curated; a seamlessly easy museum-going experience in a gorgeous I.M. Pei-designed building. I always look forward to a visit when in Bloomington. I'm sad it's closed for renovation, and look forward to its reopening.
I've only visited once, because at the time I was interested in the works of I.M. Pei and Giovanni Battista Tiepolo, but it was definitely worthwhile.

This would get five stars if the museum didn’t shut down for so long and the security wasn’t breathing down your neck. 

I’m not going to touch the art like a child, so relax.
This place is going to be awesome after it is finished from the rebuild.
The bathrooms are the most unsanitary place I've ever been and i was arrested because I'm gay and they didn't like gay people

I absolutely love Wonderlab. It's perfect for just about all age of children. It's kept clean, and there's usually something new or different for the children to grow and learn. Close to home. I'm thankful for access pass that I can be able to take them. God bless.

2nd time going for a field trip. Each time my kids loved it. I think they schedule to many schools at once, it can get pretty crowded from 10-1. Love the flame demo. The demos do have to be scheduled ahead of time.
My 6-year-old daughter loves this place! 2 stories of fun activities. She can easily spend several hours there.
It was amazing! We definitely will be back. There was so much science which is exactly what my son in into. Plus the tornado water thing !

This place is awesome for little ones. Both of my children (5 & 3) had a blast! Its like all of the hands on items from the children's museum squeezed together in one place. My children loved the bubble station and water station the best. There are a lot of hands on things for all ages. I even had fun playing in the bubbles ☺. If u are in the area, i highly recommend stopping to check it out.
Enjoyed most of the sculptures . . . some very different.  Trail a little hard to follow to be able to see all the sculptures.  Nice of them to share for free.

This place is AWESOME!! It is quite a way off the beaten path, out in the country. Google maps will take you right there, but watch how you got there because you will have ZERO service when you leave 😊. The trails are well maintained and clear. There are some hills, and a couple places have stairs, but overall I would say the trails are easy to moderate in difficulty. There are a lot of park benches spread throughout the trails. Plenty of places to take a rest and just absorb it all. There are literally tqons of sculptures all along the trail, I think there is over 130. Overall, it was a great experience, and it is good for people of all ages. I can see kids that are school age and even teens really digging it. They host pour events, where attendees can make their own sculptures. I will definitely go back!

Wow, what a find this place is! Out in the middle of nowhere Indiana (but not too far from Bloomington) is this fantastic outdoor sculpture exhibit on a grand scale in a 40+ acre beautiful mature woods. Many of the sculptures are designed and cast on site from the iron forge. They also cast aluminum too. Annual Fire event is a must see! And make your own iron bowl or plaque as well!

Great sculpture amid 2 miles of hilly walking paths through the beautiful Indiana countryside. If you visit in July, you'll be able to see the artists at work creating cast iron sculptures in the foundry, culminating at the end of the month with a spectacular Fire @ Night celebration. Highly recommend!
Phenomenal artistry. Highly recommend to anyone who appreciates art and nature. Around every bend was something that will inspire you.
Fantastic delicious food. Highly recommend the buffet. Reasonably priced for the amount and quality of food you get.
I was there for Lunch Buffet. Food was really good. I really liked the desserts. Not too sweet and very well balanced. It would be good to see some lamb options along with some Biryani.
I love the variety available on the buffet. Dinner is excellent as well. Bonus: they have a private parking lot!

Authentic Bloomington Favorite. Amazing selection and sweet PEOPLE! 
Cuisine varies nicely, diner and lunch SUPERB.

Criticisms are glassware and tables should receive more attention to detail. 
Every restaurant in Bloomington seems to need a remodel, tighten up some of those particulars and earn 5 stars. 

Yes, the personalities & ambience create the experience.

Thank you for being AUTHENTIC.

Great lunch buffet with good vegetarian options (if that's something you are looking for!) Butter chicken is also wonderful! Discount if you pay with cash. This place can be very busy and packed! There's not a lot of space to move around when it's crowded and you may have to wait a little, but the wait staff is pretty good about getting tables ready quickly - though sometimes too quickly. They tend to spray and wipe down the tables while guests are still in the process of getting up from the table and gathering their things to leave. I know it's busy and they are trying to have a quick turn around time, but it would be much better if they could at least wait until guests have left the table before cleaning.

All pros, no cons!
-Atmosphere: Warm, inviting and cozy. You can sit on cushions on the floor or at tables, or in a very nice outdoor patio.
-Service is always very fast and polite.
-Free bread, soup and tea. The soup is some of the best lentil soup I've ever had!
-Food is delicious, always cooked perfectly, ample portions with generous sides.
-Very clearly marked vegan and vegetarian options, and lots of them, all very hearty and delicious! This is one of the best restaurants in Bloomington for vegans.
-10% discount for paying in cash

The food was extremely underwhelming and I dunno where they got “award winning bread” from. It tastes like leftovers that had just been heated up. The food wasn’t bad, I just expected a ton better because of the great reviews so my expectations may have been overinflated. The place is cute, the coffee was nice, and the amount of food was insane. Lots of quantity, not much quality.

Today was my first visit to Anatolia and aside from knowing that it was Turkish food and that they had a lunch buffet I really had no idea what to expect. When I walked in the lunch buffet was served partially in a bunch of hotel pans and partially in some bowls on another table like a family picnic. Now don't let that deter you as the food was decent, initially it just did not inspire a lot of confidence in my meal choice for the day. If I were to come here again, which inevitably I'm sure I will, I will probably order off the menu rather than having the buffet mainly due in part to the fact that most of the buffet options are vegetable dishes. If you are a vegetarian this would probably please you tremendously, however I am not. Everything said the food was good the staff was polite but a little overpriced.
This is a lovely restaurant and the food is really good! The prices are great and the service is excellent! I'd recommend to anyone.

Great olives and hummus. Their fresh bread is amazing. I found the rest of their food lacking anything special. I asked for a Sprite and was informed that they only carry diet Coke... Seriously. They do give free tea with every meal, though it smelled and tasted of old lawn clippings. I think I would have rather had the diet Coke. Lol
Good pizza good breadstix. This is the place to go when you want cheap fast pizza that's not gonna leave you on the toilet or popping Tums all day.
Got black bean pizza was great. First time ever had was great for us vegetarians who want something different thanks avers
They have great buffet an good pizza great for the family
Got the wrong pizza and staff offered to send another one in an hour. Not really that helpful.
Pizza is always cooked perfectly and tastes fantastic.

I was recommended this restaurant by Google and decided to check it out when a friend recommended it as well. 

I had the "build your own" calzone and tried some of the garlic bread, both of which were great. The service was very nice and the atmosphere was quite relaxed on the day that I went there as well. I plan to visit the establishment again to try out the pizza at some point. I was expecting the pricing for the meals to be pretty high but I was pleasantly surprised when I saw that the prices were actually tractable. It was for this reason that I gave a 5-star review.

I would recommend this place if you like Italian style dishes like pasta, pizza, etc. and want to spend a reasonable amount of money.
The Alfredo was truly delicious and the specialty pizzas were both unique and great quality. Will definitely be returning!

In the past the pasta has been very good. Not today. I ordered spaghetti with meat sauce. The spaghetti was in such short pieces you couldn’t roll it on a fork. The meat sauce had almost no meat. I searched but only found large chewy pieces of tomato, a carrot, and 3 tiny specs of meat. When I mentioned to the server that I thought I didn’t get meat sauce, she talked to the chef. The chef told her that it was finely ground meat sauce and I had received the correct order. I guess the meat disappeared when it was finely ground. Don’t think I will continue going to Bucceto’s.

The teeth don't smile. They watch. The teeth stare. The teeth observe. The teeth examine. The teeth gaze. The teeth inspect. The teeth scrutinize. The teeth follow your every move.

Good place to buy paint.
Amazing pizza and friendly staff it was so good
Casa is a perfect lunch spot. Chicken tacos are great. Servers are polite and attentive. Will definitely be returning again.

A favorite place to eat. Had my bday there had a good time but beware of the icing in the face. You get free fried icecream for your birthday and it is rich but yummy. Diabetes on a plate rich. Prices are reasonable because they are large servings. Give them a try!💜
The Chipotle chimichanga was delicious! Portion sizes were big, prices were reasonable and the service was fast and friendly. Great atmosphere overall - I'll definitely be returning!

I finally found some SPICY sauce in the Midwest. None of that fake stuff that you might find like at Social. Everything tasted homemade, fresh and authentic. Reminds me of my favorite Mexican restaurants on the West Coast.

Dont get me wrong service and atmosphere is amazing. Food is also great every single time., But one thing that bothers me is when I have an intolerance to chicken. So I always order steak or ground beef. Well if something is cooked in something that has cooked chicken recently it is completely contaminated and I would get sick if I ate it like that, well as all of these types of restaurants I always get ungodly sick because none of them clean the pans before cooking someone else's meal. I got sick feeling after about 5 minutes into the meal .Meal was amazing absolutely stunning but their inability to clean pans before using for another type of meat or meal pisses me off. I paid for a meal I was sick after eating .I didn't ask for refund or free food because the meal was amazing ,but still ended up sick .

I have never experienced anything like the Crazy Horse. It’s an incredibly erotic show, but not necessarily sexual. Just as much a projection and light show as a celebration of the female body, a night at the crazy horse is a must-do once in a lifetime. The women are equally beautiful as they are talented, and the ambience is unparalleled. The intimate theatre is lined with gold, and red velvet, and reckons back to a Paris that seems forgotten. Drink champagne and enjoy.

Ridiculously overpriced, bordering on extortion. You pay HUNDREDS of euros for a 1.5h show, where half of the acts are obviously filler (a girl laying on a bed with a song playing... Girls wiggling their butts to a beat, not even dancing.) Some of the acts are fantastic, but there is an obvious dichotemy.

For drinks, a single beer or mix drink will set you back 20 euros! The cheapest bottle of wine starts at 85 euros! The food is obviously from a box and is ridiculously marked up as well (5 bites for 15 euros). They even try to sell you pics for 30 euros each.

Save your money. Go to a nice dinner with your partner, and a strip club after. You'll see more, and have paid less.

Came here for the "totally crazy" show and it was an absolutely amazing experience. The enviorment was nice and comfy, the staff was very helpful and friendly and the vicinity was very clean. The show it self was fantastic, I would highly recommend this place.

Crazy Horse has been and probably will be the most amazing Cabaret experience I will ever endure! From the seating and champagne to the dancers and acts in the show, the whole night was one to remember. It was very professional and exciting to watch. I highly recommend Crazy Horse to all who visit Paris, whether you like Cabaret or not it's an absolutely amazing experience!
Femininity at its best. Artistic beyond measure.  Beauty and creativity intertwined in one.

I got the orange chicken the first time I came to Chow Bar and it was very good. Now today was my second and the orange chicken was EXCELLENT. The only reason why I am not giving 5 stars is because the rice isn't the best. It is still good but just not the best.
The service is very very fast and the food comes out in no time at all. It is kinda sad to see how few people go inside to eat, but man so many people get take out orders it makes up for the fact.
Good "American" Chinese food in BTown. My list of good places is short, but Chow Bar makes the cut and they take the Crimson Card!

I am no longer a regular at this restaurant. I used to be for years. Lately, it seems their portions got smaller and their prices increased. I don't know maybe the waitress calculated wrong because she kept re-calculating my bill. It's disappointing because I paid for a meal yet I left hungry. This happened 3 times. The service was okay. Usually they have excellent service but the last few times I went, it was just okay. I was waiting for menus or drinks or for someone to take my order. I had to go up to the counter and order. They weren't too busy at that time. The food is still good but in my opinion, not worth the price for the portion size you get. I'm not saying you shouldn't go but I won't be. I gave them chance after chance so I'll take my business elsewhere.

My favorite American Chinese in Bloomington. I always benchmark the restaurants by getting General Tso’s Chicken, and this place’s is by far the best in my opinion. The bubble tea is good, too. We’ve enjoyed vanilla latte and Thai tea bubble teas.
always a great place for comfort food and more!

I had the Spaghetti and meatballs w/ a Tuscan chopped salad.  (Only offered specialty salads) Both were delicious.  I only gave 3 stars though because after a drink and 20% tip my bill for one was $30.  A little pricey for a plate of spaghetti and a salad.  Try added a regular garden salad w/ your entree.  1st Italian restaurant I’ve been to that didn’t.

Only had the Tiramisu. It was beautifully constructed, and presented in a lovely reusable container. The flavor was severely lacking, however. It was extraordinarily bitter, and the bowl had espresso seemingly poured into the bottom. It was too soggy, and much too bitter for either of our tastes.

Been there many times but this is the last.  Chicken parmesan like shoe leather & husband ordered a spicy shrimp meal he has had before but absolutely no spice. Server very responsive, git me a different meal, which was had a watered down Alfredo sauce.  Sad.  Used to have good food.

Solid Italian food. The caprese towers are wonderful, though they ran out of basil the other day and didn't inform me until they served them without it. I had to actually ask why there was no basil. Other than that, I've always had good service and good food.

Sicilian calzone is awesome!!! Cant wait to go back dine in and try other delicious looking meals from the menu.... Very fresh ingredients . Handmade dough is delicious, not to mention the marinated tomatoes!!!

Not bad in general. Environment is nice, staff is friendly. 

Tried lamb kabob, but not spicy. 

Next time will ask for spicy food recommendation!
I'm a huge fan of the Mediterranean fresh wrap. Visit for dinner on Tuesdays for an even better deal: 2-for-1 wraps!

Having never experienced middle eastern food prior to coming here, it was a pleasant surprise.  Add in plenty of vegan options (including gelato flavors) and a good lunch ambience, and you have an ideal option for lunch on Kirkwood.  Personally, I would recommend hummus and pita + a plate of Falafels.  Easily feeds 2 people for a cheap price of only 16-20 dollars.  Their fast service and reasonable prices are what sold me on the restaurant.
Their Shawarma is fake. I only liked their French fries. I have not tried their Falafel or other things. The cashier is lovely as she is welcoming and smiling.
Excellent food at a fair price and super fast and friendly service. Will definitely return.

I decided to eat lunch at The Irish Lion Restaurant because of the positive reviews. I got there about 12:15 PM on a Saturday. I enjoyed reading about the history of the building, pretty neat story. The menu has a lot of choices. I decided on the Irish Banger & Colcannon. It was very tasty! Since I was alone, I sat at the bar and the place was not all that busy while I was there. The only negative I have is it was difficult to get anyone to check on me to see if I wanted or needed anything. If you are on the fence, I would recommend you give it a try.

Absolutely my most favorite place to eat in all of Indiana. The food is the closest I've had to authentic pub food in Ireland. The Guinness is always on point and they offer droughts by the pint, pitcher, 1/2 yard, and full yard (which are a fun game to drink in themselves). They offer unique seating options in the main bar area, as well as upstairs and patio options. I've opted to drive an hour and a half (each way) just to go to this place for dinner on several occasions. A "must go" if you're in Bloomington.

The Irish Lion is a fantastic pub. The food is good, and the atmosphere is terrific. Prices are excellent. If you are visiting without kids, opt for the downstairs. The upstairs is good but the service is slow and the ambiance is not quite as good.

I've loved this place since I was in college. The food is great and the atmosphere is really comfortable and friendly. I always feel like I'm at a gathering of friends and family when I'm here. There's lots of good Irish/British food on the menu, including some more adventurous options like escargot. They also serve pretty good oysters for a pub in the Midwest.

They have separate parts of the restaurant for families and the 21 and over lot, so if you're looking to avoid the potentially roudier lot you can definitely do that.

Their drink menu is extensive and good. I'm not big on beer so I can't speak to that selection, but their collection of scotch and whiskey is nothing to sneeze at. They also do flights if you're not sure what sounds best. All in all, the Irish Lion is a place for great experiences, and I always make sure to visit at least once whenever I'm in town.

Like that is an old structure  so that is something  special  and different.  I like their food. I had the prime rib and it was cooked properly  and tasted  good. Like that you have opinions to mix the beers  which is fun to do. Definitely worth trying out.

Janko's is a Bloomington institution. Hands down the best steakhouse in town. They do have vegetarian options, but that is definitely not the draw. They also only serve wine and beer - no mixed drinks. The wine selection is extensive and their beer selection good. I celebrate my birthday every year at Janko's, except when it falls on a Sunday.

Nice steak house under the ambiance of a more college vibe. Service was attentive and nice, checking in several times without feeling over bearing. Nice wine selection served at appropriate temps for red. Meatballs are good golf ball size and with a slightly spicy red sauce. Ribeye steak was large and cooked great with grill marks charred perfectly. Ordered it medium rare and although it was cooked more rare the pink center was still great. Lamb chops were cooked a perfect medium rare, juicy and seasoned. The potatoes are just basic but compliments to the entrees none the less. Enjoyed my experience

Have been there numerous times. We always get the steaks....high quality beef and cooked to perfection.  Accompanied by a baked potato and salad. Of course, there are other offerings, but steak is their thing. Not a fancy atmosphere by any means, so don't expect that. And, yes...it's loud and hectic. You most definitely need reservations, particularly on weekends and college events. But....the food is outstanding and consistent, and the service is impeccable.

Tonight our family of 17 had a wonderful meal at Janko’s celebrating a family birthday. Our food was delicious and all of our steaks were cooked to perfection! Our service was outstanding! Still a great place to eat!!!!  Can’t remember when or if I had a better steak!

This is definitely more of a casual place. it kind of reminds me of a small pizza place in Chicago with checkerboard tablecloths and no frills atmosphere. It was a little disappointing that they didn't have a full liquor bar but the huge wine list made up for it. I felt the price was a little high for a casual place, but the food more than made up for that. I had the New York and my friend had a filet. Both were amazing. I'll definitely be back next time I'm in town.

This place has went down hill. I walk in the greeting isn't the best. As tho they don't even care if you are there. I don't like that service could be a lot better. It use to be, I'm deeply concerned. I don't think I'll be back to eat here. I expect service to be great. Not this subpar service. It's not like it's just one of the employees it's most of them. I definitely won't be back and I'm taking away more stars. The insides beautiful but it's rather dirty. It's possible that they just didn't like my kind.

Fantastic food and atmosphere. Our drinks were out in under 3 minutes and quite generous with the pour. The food was pretty standard for Mexican food,  but the quality was pretty solid and delicious. Left feeling fullfilled and could easily go back again for more.

Was so pleasing to the eye I didnt even want to eat it 😊 I did though. It was delicious and staff was friendly and helpful with menu questions. Charming place with a lounge that I'll have to visit some day.

The chips and salsa were great, especially the green hot salsa, it had excellent flavor.  I had a 3 enchilada plate.  The chicken with green sauce was very good.  The beef with white cheese sauce was ok and the cheese with red sauce not so much.  We're really not fans if this melted white American cheese.  I don't know if it's an Indiana Mexican food thing or what but it is not Mexican cheese.
Quick service, clean,  solid little restaurant. Art work is nice, the overall feel is like a lounge from the 70s or something. Ask for the extra spicy salsa.

Fantastic food, fantastic service. Everyone is extremely friendly and answered all of my questions, and the food was delicious and freshly prepared. A great place for any collage kid looking for some dinner or lunch. Definitely a new favorite place for a quick bite!
One of my favorite places to eat in Bloomington! The ambiance is cheery, and the food is fresh and original. Love the Thai burrito with chicken and the tropical fruit salsa.
I enjoyed the Backyard BBQ burrito and had a good lunch.  Cool place!
The best atmosphere. I never had organic anything until I ate here. The burritos are huge and filling. Absolutely delicious. They could have better drink selections. But definitely will be back!
We loved the laughing planet!! So many delicious choices. You can make your own burrito or pick off their menu. Food was really good and the services was good.

We had the waffles and the brunch bowl, both were delicious. I had the waffles and even though the scrambled eggs looked plain they fit perfectly into the bowl with the wild arrangement of flavors. It even made me jealous after my first two bites of the bowl. Staff is very polite, humorous and accommodating, I'm picky about my tables and requested a change. :)
Would definitely return.
Food, service, and atmosphere were amazing! Recommended to us by our Airbnb host & was definitely worth a trip. A little pricey but you get what you pay for in quality & quantity!

Quoted a 30 minute wait - actual only half that. Love the under promise, over deliver!

Great service. Not a pest but always there when needed.

Very tight seating, but not uncomfortable.

Excellent appetizer choices, really tasty eggplant parmesan, and one of the best pizzas we have had in Bloomington, and that's saying something.

Very good, large salads.

Will return eagerly.
Nice selection of craft beers, great menu for every craving, comfortable place for friends and family. Locally owned, sustainably-minded and friendly service.

Lennie's is a Bloomington treasure. The food is fantastic, the beer delightful, and the service is impeccable. One of my regular meals is the wings with a side salad. The best wings in Bloomington hands down, and the best house salad I've had anywhere. Try the roasted red pepper vinaigrette; you won't be sorry. The pizza is a great choice if you like thin crust and delicious sauce. You only need to save a little room for dessert, because they have the perfect sized dessert shooters. That's what I call them - can't recall their name for them. But they're the perfect size - like a double shot of deliciousness. I highly recommend the chocolate mousse. But don't hesitate to try whatever the special is. I truly love this place and recommend it to locals and visitors alike. All are welcome and treated with great food, drink, and kindness.

This is me and my wife's absolute favorite place in the world! We have been there a lot and we have never had a bad experience. If your thinking about trying it out DO IT!! You won't be disappointed. Get a bowl of Beef Pho and your all set!! Seriously the best place EVER!!
Must try this place! The amazingly sweet owner is from Burma and the food is so delicious! A lot of the ingredients used in the dishes are imported from Burma and authentic! Highly recommend!
Great Food! They have a picture menu. The tealeaf salad is a must-try.
The food was really good, nothing fancy but good bang for your buck. It (and all restarants by there) are not lucensed to serve alcohol.

If I have to pinpoint my favorite Bloomington restaurant, it would definitely be Burma Garden. I've gone multiple times in the last 2 years and the food never disappoints. In addition, the quality and service is always consistent. The owners are always willing to accommodate dietary needs/preferences and offer alternatives to dishes as I am a vegetarian.

I've posted my most frequented dishes below: curry eggplant and ohn no khao swe. My boyfriend gets the ohn no khao swe every time and absolutely loves it. The curry eggplant melts in your mouth and goes great with the coconut rice.
Sushi was terrible. The place seemed nice & the guy helping me was nice, but the sushi was truly disgusting. I’ve had better from a grocery store

Nice, clean, pretty restaurant, but the food was just kind of okay. EXCEPT FOR THE ROASTED DUCK IN THAI BASIL AND COCONUT MILK, it was INCREDIBLE!!!
 We had pad thai, appetizer sampler and sushi too but all was just kind of okay.
Food is always great, but tonight I had a new waiter. He had pretty long nails. Kind of ruined the mood when I noticed his long nails on my plate. Just kind of grossed me out.
Pad thai. Spicy chicken. Red curry. Drunken mans fried rice. Would recommend them all.  All delicious!!
Good food but you have to ask for extra chili sauce!
Our good friend took us there for lunch. The place was packed but the service and the quality of the food was great. It was a buffet but the food was fresh and wholesome. A great place to eat.

The atmosphere was very nice as were the waitresses. The food came in a timely manner, and was absolutely amazing. I was a little afraid before going that there wouldn’t be a lot of food for the price (we ordered from the menu), but, in my opinion, you get a lot of really good food (I even needed a takeout box). Our meal was very flavorful and very nicely made. Definitely going to eat here again in the future!

This was our first time at the restaurant. The ambience was good and the taste of the food was great. I wouldn't say it's authentic Mediterranean but nevertheless the food was a treat to the taste buds. The kebabs especially, chicken and lamb, were good and I would definitely recommend those. The waitress was very courteous and did excellent in her service. My 8 year old son usually never eats much in restaurants but it was surprising to see him enjoy his soup, the bread and the sambosas!! Overall, I will definitely recommend this to anyone who like to try different cuisines once in a while.

I'm very impressed and will definitely be back. I got the sampler plate that came with a little bit of everything and like almost everything quite a bit. I can't be more specific because I never remember the names of things but I'll try to remember next time I'm in...

Great lunch buffet. Nice dinner spot for Afghani food in a fancy setting. There are plenty of options here for vegetarians. I however love lamb, and samira is the best place in town for lamb. I would recommend a dish, but I've had several, and all of them have been great. Portions are generous as well. They give baklava with the buffet, and it is delicious.

My husband and I just celebrated our anniversary here, and our experience was wonderful. First of all, the food was amazing. Second of all, as someone with multiple food allergies, eating out is not always a pleasant or easy experience. When my husband made the reservation he also mentioned my allergies, and when our waiter came to the table he not only already knew exactly what my allergies were, but was prepared to make suggestions as to what I could and could not tweak on the menu, even making personal suggestions as to what wouldn't be quite as good with the necessary adjustments. I have never had this experience anywhere else, and was very impressed with the service we received.

This is my absolute favorite restaurant in Bloomington.  Chef Tallent is an absolute genius when it comes to building and combining really unique, deep flavors.  Also a really nice guy who frequently find a few minutes to wander the restaurant and say hi to everyone.
Great food, great service, and exceptional wine list. Every visit is a new experience.
Agnolotti was way too spicy.  Other than that, delicious as usual!
I have never had such amazing food.  I'm a snotty snob and I loved this place.
